/*! \mainpage

What is Bobura?
===============

Bobura is some software about railways.


What is Tetengo2?
=================

Tetengo2 is a kind of GUI toolkit.


Requirements
============

Bobura
------

- Windows 7 or later

Tetengo2
--------

Tetengo2 is available on Windows and UNIX-like systems.

It's tested on the following systems:

- Windows 7 Service Pack 1
- Debian GNU/Linux 7.0
- Cygwin 1.7.17

How to Build
============

Only the source code of Bobura and Tetengo2 are distributed for the time being.

Downloading the Source Code Archive
-----------------------------------

The latest archives can be downloaded from
[the web site](http://www.tetengo.org/).

Cloning the Repository
----------------------

You can clone the Git repository like this:

~~~~{.sh}
$ git clone http://github.com/kaorut/bobura.git
~~~~

Building on Windows
-------------------

You need the following tools in order to build Bubura and Tetengo2:

- [Visual C++ 2012 Update 2](http://www.microsoft.com/)
- [Boost C++ Libraries 1.53.0](http://www.boost.org/)
- [bzip2](http://www.bzip.org)
- [Doxygen 1.8.4](http://www.doxygen.org) (to generate API document)
- [Graphviz](http://www.graphviz.org) (to generate API document)


Building on UNIX
----------------

You need the following tools in order to build Bubura and Tetengo2:

- [GCC 4.7.2](http://www.gnu.org/)
- [GNU Make](http://www.gnu.org/)
- [Boost C++ Libraries 1.53.0](http://www.boost.org/)
- [bzip2](http://www.bzip.org)
- [Doxygen 1.8.4](http://www.doxygen.org) (to generate API document)
- [Graphviz](http://www.graphviz.org) (to generate API document)

When you clone the Git repository, you will not find the `configure` script in
the working copy.
Run `bootstrap.sh` to produce the `configure` script.
`bootstrap.sh` requires the following tools:

- [Autotools (Autoconf, Automake, etc.)](http://www.gnu.org/)
- [Autoconf Archive](http://www.gnu.org/)

~~~~{.sh}
$ ./bootstrap.sh
~~~~

